faqs.question: How do I reset my password?
faqs.answer: You can reset your password by clicking on the 'Forgot Password' link on the login page and following the instructions.

faqs.question: What should I do if I encounter a technical issue?
faqs.answer: If you face any technical issues, contact our support team through the 'Help' section or email us at support@example.com.

faqs.question: Is my personal information secure?
faqs.answer: Yes, we prioritize user security and adhere to strict privacy standards to ensure your data is safe.

faqs.question: Can I use this platform on mobile devices?
faqs.answer: Yes, our platform is fully responsive and works seamlessly on mobile devices.

faqs.question: How can I contact customer support?
faqs.answer: You can contact customer support via our 'Contact Us' page or by emailing support@example.com.

faqs.question: How do I ban or delete an event?
faqs.answer: To ban or delete an event, navigate to the 'Event Management' section, find the event, and select 'Ban' or 'Delete'.

faqs.question: Can I manage user permissions?
faqs.answer: Yes, you can manage user permissions in the 'User Management' section under the admin dashboard.

faqs.question: How do I generate reports?
faqs.answer: Go to the 'Reports' section, select the desired report type, and download or view it directly.

faqs.question: What happens when I ban an organizer?
faqs.answer: When you ban an organizer, they are unable to create or manage events, and their account will be flagged.

faqs.question: How do I monitor event performance?
faqs.answer: Event performance can be monitored in the 'Event Analytics' section, where you can view attendance, sales, and ratings.

faqs.question: How do I book tickets for an event?
faqs.answer: To book tickets, browse through the events, select your preferred one, and proceed with the payment on the event page.

faqs.question: What is the refund policy?
faqs.answer: Refunds are available for canceled or banned events. Please check our refund policy for more details.

faqs.question: How do I view my booked tickets?
faqs.answer: You can view your booked tickets under the 'My Tickets' section on your dashboard.

faqs.question: Can I transfer my ticket to someone else?
faqs.answer: Currently, ticket transfers are not allowed. Please contact support for special cases.

faqs.question: How do I rate an event I attended?
faqs.answer: After attending an event, go to the 'My Tickets' section, find the event, and submit your rating and feedback.

faqs.question: How do I create an event?
faqs.answer: To create an event, go to the 'My Events' section, click on 'Create Event', and fill out the required details.

faqs.question: What are the requirements for event approval?
faqs.answer: Events must comply with our guidelines, including accurate descriptions, valid venues, and appropriate content.

faqs.question: How do I view ticket sales for my events?
faqs.answer: Go to the 'My Events' section, select the event, and click on 'Sales Report' to view ticket sales.

faqs.question: What should I do if my event is banned?
faqs.answer: If your event is banned, you will receive a notification with the reason. Contact support for further assistance.

faqs.question: How do I promote my event?
faqs.answer: You can promote your event by using our platform's marketing tools, including featured listings and social media integrations.
